<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-766-127  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 766 127.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Dec 13 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Prime joins IT companies siting support in Australia. (Prime joinsinformation technology firms, offers new customer support center)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zucker, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Prime Computer Inc. (Location).andO;Ticker:    PRM.andO;Topic:     Support ServicesService BureausMultinational CorporationFacility LocationAustraliaComputer industry.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>PRIME JOINS IT COMPANIES SITING SUPPORT IN AUSTRALIA 12/13/90 SYDNEY,AUSTRALIA, 1990 DEC 13 (NB) -- Prime is to site its third global support sitein Sydney.andP;  The company will join a number of others (such asHewlett-Packard) which already have major support sites in Australia.andP;  One ofthe main reasons is that it represents the third time zone -- the others areNorth America and Europe.andP;  This is especially important for supporting sitesin Japan and the rest of Asia, since they on similar times to Australia.andM;In Prime's case, the other two sites are US and Germany.andP;  The Australian sitewill cover Asia, as far as India.andP;  By early 1991 Prime hopes to have anautomatic 24-hour assistance system, where calls are routed to the centre onduty.andM;Another advantage of widely distributed support centres is that they can dodouble shifts when disaster hits the primary support centre or itscommunications.andM;(Paul Zucker/19901213)</TEXT></DOC>